Description:
THE AVANTE-GARDE OF OFFICER PROPERTIES
"From the refined architecture of Alsace to the views like that of the Pyrénées - Paris is just on your door step at 28 Toddington Avenue."
Bonjour, and welcome to quintessential French living whilst enjoying the comforts and benefits of the area's premier estate.
The property is adorned with French provincial characteristics including classical cornices, double-doors, white window shutters and a kitchen that fuses rustic French towns with Parisian suburban designs.
However, it must be mentioned the 12-month-old home doesn't forego contemporary features that define modern living.
Located in the premier estate of Timbertop the property is adjacent to sprawling parkland, walking distance to Officer's newest primary school (opening next year) and close to shops and train stations.
The 30.51sqm property itself features:
- 4 large bedrooms, master with en-suite and walk-in robe;
- Theatre room;
- Rumpus room;
- Open plan living/dining room that encapsulates an abundance of natural light;
- Lifted ceilings;
- Down lights throughout;
- An encompassing alfresco that gazes over the sprawling hills and watches peacefully as the sun rises in the east and sinks in the west;
- Double car garage;
- Genuine side access;
- Large block that spans just under 700sqm (one of the largest in the early Timbertop releases).
Add on top of this additional extras like:
- Ducted heating and evaporative cooling;
- Security door system;
- Gas fire place that looks like a genuine fire;
- Ducted vacuum system.
The list could continue into the night. To save you reading further, how about you just book in your European getaway to Toddington now?
Ray White prides itself on being as accurate as possible however anyone considering purchasing the property should undertake their own due diligence to confirm the above.

MODERN, COSY AND PRIME LOCATION!
"Have you ever enjoyed a night out at D'Angelo winery and wondered how you're getting home? Well when you live 100 metres from Officer's premier establishment you'd need not worry any more."
Walking distance to St Brigids Primary School and public transport plus a couple of somersaults from the D'Angelo Winery this neat and tidy four bedroom home has everything you'd want. Plus more.
Outside you will find well landscaped gardens and plants as well as a large covered deck with ceiling fan.
As you enter you will be impressed by the space and quality this home offers.
Featuring:
- Large master bedroom with en-suite and walk in robe;
- Formal living room;
- Open plan kitchen living with floating floorboards;
- Kitchen complete with stone bench tops, ample bench space and stainless steel appliances, including microwave;
- Kids retreat/third living room;
- Ducted heating & evaporative cooling;
- Double garage with internal access;
- Alarm System;
- Quality blinds
The house-proud tenants would love to stay on so investors here is your chance to secure a wonderful home with matching occupants.
Ray White prides itself on being as accurate as possible however anyone considering purchasing the property should undertake their own due diligence to confirm the above.

LOVE STORY IN ROWLING DRIVE
"A place in this world for you to finally call home."
Located in the enchanted estate of Arcadia is a gorgeous 3 bedroom home that is so close to everything. What was a few years ago blank space and paddocks is now schools, shops and a bursting mini metropolis full of vibrant culture. It's even a stone throw away from the Christmas Tree Farm. Immerse yourself in the change.
The lucky one who purchases this property will also get the added benefit of a house that's only a few years old and is finished with style.
Complete with low maintenance gardens and a well-designed floor plan with schools the house features:
- Master bedroom with en-suite and walk-in robe;
- Remaining 2 bedrooms with built-in robes;
- Open plan living/dining room;
- Kitchen complete with stainless steel appliances and dishwasher;
- Ducted heating throughout;
- Evaporative cooling;
- Decked entertaining area;
- 1 and half car garage with internal access
Come for the inspection, stay, stay, stay for the house.
